    "body": "As mentioned in https://github.com/trufflesuite/ganache-cli/issues/800#issuecomment-720129628 this is confirmed to be happening.\r\n\r\nTried adding a test for it, but we have another bug in `soltest`/`isoltest`:\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract C {\r\n        function f() public {\r\n                revert(\"\"); \r\n        }\r\n}\r\n// ====\r\n// EVMVersion: >=byzantium\r\n// compileViaYul: also\r\n// revertStrings: debug\r\n// ----\r\n// f() -> FAILURE, hex\"08c379a0\", 0x20, 0, \"\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `\"\"` field is not recognized and is replaced with `\"string\"`, but that doesn't matches the value ðŸ˜¬ ",
